===================================
Applying a specific selection for ZZ
===================================

MCFM  Example Tested with MCFM 6.2


Steps 
1) Create a ZZ_cut.f file inside MCFM/src/User
2) Modify gencuts.f
3) Modify the makefile
e.g add ZZ_cuts under USERFILES

USERFILES = \
ZZ_cuts.o \
cdfhwwcuts.o \
 
4) Re-compile
5) Add the needed string to the MCFM options file e.g. the .DAT file/

The example tries to mirror  the PowHeg selections :

1) m_12 >12 m_34 >12 Pt > 5 for all leptons --> gg filter

"ATLASZZ10"

2) m_ll>4GeV between all same-flavour opposite-sign pairs and at least 3 leptons with pT>5GeV

"ATLASZZ20" for mumu-ee when same flavour opposite-sign is unique
"ATLASZZ21" for mumu-mumu ee-ee  when same flavour opposite-sign are not unique

3) m_ll>4GeV between all same-flavour opposite-sign pairs and at least 3 leptons with pT>5GeV

"ATLASZZ30" for mumu-ee when same flavour opposite-sign is unique
"ATLASZZ31" for mumu-mumu ee-ee  when same flavour opposite-sign are not unique

Note that given the changed gencuts, one overwrites  further cuts , so the "analysis"
must be done in the ZZ_cuts file.






